caption: I am writing this because feel it is necessary to warn others. I am 100 percent positive it was the quality of chicken they served at this place that made me sick . My advise to customers if you are reading this , choose somewhere else. It’s simply not worth it. If you work at China star and are reading this , serve better food and I suspect some of your food is over due dates do not serve it to anyone ..
The food is great, and the price is reasonable.
Same as it has always been. And it's Chinese food at reasonable prices.
Food is very bland.  Minimum order is $15.  Even for pickup.  Rude staff doesn't speak English.  Guess you can't have good Asian food on Mondays.  Just saying.
Fast, fresh, and delicious Chinese food. Authentic Chinese options and very affordable with complimentary hot tea.

China Star had good food. I personally wasn't fond of the egg rolls. You can enter China Star from both sides of the building decide by US Bank and chipotle the door has a hallway to the front once you get to the other side there is a storefront on the other side of the building
Really good broccoli beef with rice and fortune cookie, tastes best eaten with chopsticks. Fresh veggies and loaded up for about six dollars.
Convenient location. Food prepared fresh to order and served hot. Cash only.

Went for lunch today to give it a try. I asked for sesame chicken with chow mein. The cashier pointed at the menu indicating different options just confusing me (this was my first time ordering/wasn’t sure what to get). Not to mention I couldn’t really understand her english. Well, when I finally sat to eat my food I got a box with sesame chicken & fried rice & another with white rice & a weird mix of vegetables. I asked for chow mein thinking i’d get noodles. Chicken & Fried rice was good, but they definately messed up my order. Why would they not include noodles in chow mein??
You need to order house special lo mein, mini hotpot, szechuan chicken, sweet and garlic chicken and egg drop soup (add hot sauce) here.

I love this place. Foods great, done fast, people are nice. I'd say the only downside is they only take cash, but that's not too big of a deal for me. This place is set as my favorite Chinese restaurant.
I mean you get what you pay for. But for a meal that costs <$6, this place sure gives you a lot. I eat here weekly, never disappointed.
More Egg Roles!! :)
Mongolian Beef more like Mongoodlian  Beef.

I went here after a play rehearsal tonight. Despite getting there at easily 9:15 but probably more like 9:30, my meal was made fresh and the staff was really friendly. I got a small hot and sour soup and a sesame chicken to go and was incredibly impressed by the portion size. I ended up being full after the soup, because there was so much good stuff in it! The standout items in it which pleasantly surprised me (as you don't tend to find them in hot and sour) were water chestnuts and little bits of chicken. Although I'm saving most of it for leftovers, the sesame chicken is also very good: the sauce is light but incredibly flavorful, and they give you a few pieces of broccoli as well. Overall, I am very impressed and will definitely be coming back!

Great food at great prices. They have both american Chinese food and a special menu that includes hot pots. Would highly recommend the garlic shrimp. My only recommendation is that they start taking credit and debit cards.
Many good dishes, but not all are good. Spicy chicken is my favorite.
Eat here every day. Cheapest food in the mall and good!
Great little place with freshly cooked lunch specials for just under $6 (including tax). Huge menu.
Very good food.

My roommates and I go here every week. The lunch special is an amazing deal and the atmosphere is great. The food tastes incredible both fresh from the kitchen and even the next day if I bring any home to reheat. I would consider China star an important part of my college experience.
Love the curry and ragoons. Been here many time and while they don't take cards it's still amazing.
Pretty good food. Really liked the taste.
Homie behind the desk was dope. Good food

It's a great cheap Chinese fast food place. They only take cash and have big portion sizes. The cashiers seem to really care about whole-dollar amounts. A lot of their menu is set up so that things come out nearly even to the dollar, e.g. if your order comes out to $7.04 they'll just have you pay $7 instead of breaking a dollar into cents.
Great food and the staff is very kind.

(Translated by Google) The place supports Alipay and WeChat Pay, and 517 takeaways are also available for self-collection Recommendation: Fried chicken wings (affordable) Braised pork in braised hot pot can also be tried, but the price is higher  (Original) 该地支持支付宝与微信支付 亦可517外卖自取 推荐：炸鸡翅（实惠） 红烧肉 火锅亦可一试，唯价格较高
Fire
Good food - accepts cash only
Food is plain. Found hair in my bean curd lunch.
Made me love Asian food!
Delicious food, but was not clean and had plastic silverware
The best Chinese food in Waterloo, Iowa. Friendly service. Clean eating area. Food was perfect. Definitely recommend!!
Staff was rude.  Credit cards not accepted. Food was terrible.  Please don’t waste your time and money.
Best take out American style Chinese in Iowa City. Fast and tasty.
Worst Chinese I’ve ever had.  Tasteless.  No flavor and was to be spicy.  Poor quality chicken .  Gross.
Delicious and a variety of Chinese food

This is my favorite place in town to get Chinese food. It's good food at a low price. I order chicken and broccoli with steamed rice. That meal is $5.75 and it's enough to fill me up, which is saying something, because I like to eat a lot.

This used to be my favorite Chinese in Iowa City, but I'm the last year, the chicken quality has been less than good. Still good price and convenient for work lunch. They do not accept anything but can though.

This is our go-to Chinese takeout in Iowa City. We love China Star for their consistently and value. You can’t go wrong with their generous lunch combo for under six dollars. The Kung Pao Chicken, Lo mein, and egg rolls here are the best in town. They also serve a wide variety of authentic dishes.

Good Chinese food. Great for take-out or a quick bite while in downtown Iowa City. I like their appetizers including egg rolls and great egg drop soup. The beef and broccoli is tasty.  The sesame chicken is great for kids since it is sweet and not to spicy. They also offer hot pots. They are located inside Old Capitol Town Center which offers the first hour of parking free in the attached parking ramp.
I enjoy what I get there and think the service is fast and affordable for the amount of food you’re given.
Served me reheated food and ended up getting sick from it, never going here again.
Best place to go for Chinese in Iowa City. Love the staff and the food
Food is okay, but check that they give you the correct change. Stealing from your customers isn't okay.

Excellent  Chinese food in town. You should order from their Chinese menu. Ask for it, recently they have translated that menu in English. Items on their original English menu are not that good. However items on their Chinese menu are delicious! FYI, they accept cash only.
Great Chinese Food! Reasonably priced but cash only.
Open early in the morning, fast, cheap price, and quite enough portion for breakfast or lunch!
Great service
The cashier was very rude to me and the food was gross. NEVER AGAIN WILL I GO HERE!

I ordered the Chicken Fried rice because that is my go to at Chinese restaurants. Okay let's just say that chicken fried rice is my favorite food in the entire world, and I've eaten chicken fried rice from many places. Also I can't speak for all of their dishes but the chicken fried rice from this place was the worst i have ever tasted. It tasted STALE. You know the taste food can get when you leave it uncovered in the refrigerator? well it tasted like that!
The General Tso's chicken is generous enough to feed two large eaters and very tasty. Can't speak for any other dishes. Prices are a bit expensive if eating by yourself.

Wanted nomis in Solon but they are closed on Mondays so thought I'd try this place but when I called in they don't understand english... made ordering extremely hard and they said they don't know what soy sauce is...
Good chinese very consistent only place we eat chinese in Iowa city.

Momma said: say nothing if you need to criticize.  Forgive me momma.  Egg roll was good.  General Tso's chicken was bland, crunchy small chunks of chicken, served with broccoli (tasted sour- pure yuck).  Yellow Rice hohum and crab Rangoon was so thin it almost appeared 2 dimensional with very little taste. Yikes !!!  Even the fortune cookie tasted stale. If anyone would have eaten that meal and recommended it or the restaurant, I  would suggest that they try to get out more.  Again I say, sorry momma!
(Translated by Google) Very good place  (Original) 挺好一地方

I only ever go at lunch, you can get a heaping plate of good chinese food for under six bucks. It's always very busy in there, but they get the food out in less than 10 minutes! The staff is sort of to the point, not super friendly but they always seem to be super busy. Overall a great place for a fast lunch.

As a college student, I am a huge fan of China Star. Their whole menu is very reasonably priced, and most things are very, very tasty. If you're looking to get bang for your buck, their lunch special is the best deal on campus--25 different dishes that are under $6. China Star also serves some very high quality Chinese food, but it comes at a price.
Nice place to eat lunch. Cash only.

Horrible service.  I ordered garlic chicken; then I asked if it was a spicy dish.  The cashier said no, and then she said it was mildly spicy.  I told her that I didn’t want it to be spicy hot, so she said she would tell the kitchen to hold the hot.  Now I can stand some pretty spicy food, but I don’t enjoy the really, really spicy stuff.  I got it to go, so when I got to my destination, I started to eat it and it was more than 5-alarm spicy hot!!  I could not eat it.  My husband enjoys spicy food so I saved it for him and even he couldn’t eat much of it (he said he was pretty sure they put habanero peppers in it).  The spice was way above and beyond anything we have ever experienced with an order of garlic chicken, so I’m pretty sure that someone loaded it up with peppers and spices on purpose!  I won’t be back!!

I don't care what anyone says about this place. Every time I have visited the food has been very good and the atmosphere charming. Yes, it's a bummer they don't accept plastic but when I have cash I'm taking myself to China Star!!
Stringy chicken

These people charge $11 for a plate of chinese fast food?  No thank you.  They only take cash, which is not at all handy for plastic-only students like myself.  Plus, the help is very rude, and the atmosphere is very loud and unpleasant.
